Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Lock
    The Lock class goes beyond the general concept of lock because it can either represent a lock currently being held, or a lock which hasn't been acquired yet, in latter case, it serves as a container storing the information which will be used later
    Manager
    The Manager class is use as a Transaction Manager, it has the main methods needed to control transactions in the database.
    Parser
    The Parser class read and parse the commands from the commands file, call the needed functions in other class for processing
    Site
    The Site class contains all the variables and functions needed for a site in a distributed database, including the locks.
    Transaction
    The transaction class is contains all the functions and variables needed for the transaction for the distributed database, including locks.
    Variable
    The Variable class is contains all the functions and variables needed for the variables for the distributed database, including the locks.
